Finding.Solution:
Update all requirements to conform to SRP 3.3:
(a) Add a type attribute to each <Requirement>, e.g. <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.1" type="FR"> and <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.1.1" type="NFR">;
(b) Remove the inner <Type> child tags or keep them only as redundant documentation if allowed by process, but the canonical type must be the attribute;
(c) Normalize HL-EXPL-1.1 Type to a single valid value or mark it explicitly as a non-implementable example outside the normal requirement set (e.g., remove it from the HLR list, or set type="NFR" and change its content/name to clarify its purpose).
